title: Bitcoin just had its best day ever — Is $100K BTC price programmed?
description:
Analysts expect Bitcoin price to breach $150,000 by the end of 2025, driven by the upcoming halving and the demand introduced by Bitcoin ETFs.

Bitcoin (BTC) had its highest daily close at $68,245 on March 4, beating its previous record close of $67,525 on Nov. 8, 2021. The world’s first cryptocurrency is up over 18% on the weekly and 55% on the monthly chart.

Does this mean that Bitcoin price is on track to reach $100,000 by the end of the year? Some analysts are expecting even higher price levels, while others are anticipating a local top at the all-time high price resistance of $69,000.

The new price-agnostic demand introduced by United States spot Bitcoin exchange-traded funds (ETFs) will help the world’s largest crypto breach its previous all-time high, according to a research report by Bitfinex Analysts, shared with Cointelegraph. Notably:

title: SEC seeks public comments on Ethereum ETF, raises concerns on proof of stake
description: The SEC is inviting public comments to help them assess the "nature" of Ethereum and whether proof of stake opens an ETF to possible fraud.
